From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] clk: sunxi-ng: suniv: reparent VE clock to PLL_VE

The suniv CCU models the VE gate as a child of pll-audio, with a TODO
noting it should most likely be pll-ve. On F1C200s hardware the video
engine demonstrably follows PLL_VE's rate, so make pll-ve the parent.

Deliberately NO CLK_SET_RATE_PARENT: with rate propagation enabled,
every decoder start live-reprograms PLL_VE (cedrus asks 297 MHz,
libcedarc asks 300 MHz). Without it, those clk_set_rate() calls are
absorbed by the gate and the engine runs at PLL_VE's power-on default
of 210 MHz (24 MHz * 35 / 4) - the exact behaviour of the validated
6.6 image. Hardware testing showed no stability difference between
the two (a separate cedrus VLD-poll hang was the real lockup source),
but 210 MHz is the long-proven operating point, so keep it. If more
VE headroom is ever needed, set PLL_VE once at boot via DT
assigned-clock-rates instead of re-enabling live propagation.

Signed-off-by: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu-suniv-f1c100s.c | 12 +++++++-----
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu-suniv-f1c100s.c
+++ b/drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu-suniv-f1c100s.c
@@ -308,10 +308,15 @@
 				       0x120, 0, 4, 8, 3, BIT(15), 0);
 
 /*
- * TODO: BSP says the parent is pll-audio, however common sense and experience
- * told us it should be pll-ve. pll-ve is totally not used in BSP code.
+ * The BSP structures name pll-audio here, but on real F1C100s/F1C200s
+ * hardware the video engine follows PLL_VE's rate, so the gate feeds
+ * from PLL_VE. Deliberately no CLK_SET_RATE_PARENT: the VE drivers'
+ * clk_set_rate() calls are absorbed and the engine runs at PLL_VE's
+ * power-on default of 210 MHz (24 MHz * 35 / 4), the operating point
+ * validated on this hardware. Use DT assigned-clock-rates on PLL_VE
+ * if a different fixed rate is ever needed.
  */
-static SUNXI_CCU_GATE(ve_clk, "ve", "pll-audio", 0x13c, BIT(31), 0);
+static SUNXI_CCU_GATE(ve_clk, "ve", "pll-ve", 0x13c, BIT(31), 0);
 
 static SUNXI_CCU_GATE(codec_clk, "codec", "pll-audio", 0x140, BIT(31), 0);
 
